==English==

=== Etymology ===
{{F.}} ''[[pornographie]]''; from [[Greek]] ''[[porne]]'' "prostitute" + ''[[graphien]]'' "to write"

===Noun===
'''pornography''' ([[uncountable]])
# An [[explicit]] [[depiction]] of [[eroticism]], presented with the intention of sexually exciting the viewer.
# Materials containing sexually explicit subject matter.
# Any written work with no [[literary]] significance beyond sexual stimulation.
# A [[lurid]] depiction or description intended to arouse interest or emotion (negative [[connotation]].)

